ma Thingaha]].{{citation needed|date=July 2014}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Ivan Srebrenjak]]\n* [[List of places named after Josip Broz Tito]]\n* [[:Category:Yugoslav politicians|List of Yugoslav politicians]]\n*[[Foibe massacres]]\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Politics|World War II|Socialism|Communism|Catholicism|Croatia|Serbia|Slovenia}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{reflist|20em|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"springer\">{{cite book\n  |title      = Dictionary of Minor Planet Names \u2013 (1550) Tito\n  |last       = Schmadel | first = Lutz D.\n  |publisher  = Springer Berlin Heidelberg\n  |page       = 123\n  |date       = 2007\n  |isbn       = 978-3-540-00238-3\n  |doi       = 10.1007/978-3-540-29925-7_1551 |chapter       = (1550) Tito }}</ref>\n\n}} <!-- end of reflist -->\n\n==Bibliography==\n{{refbegin|2}}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Auty\n  | first = Phyllis\n  | title = Tito: A Biography\n  | url = https://archive.org/details/titobiography00auty\n  | url-access = registration\n  | year = 1970\n  | location = New York City\n  | publisher = McGraw-Hill\n  | oclc = 100536\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Banac\n  | first = Ivo\n  | title = With Stalin against Tito: Cominformist splits in Yugoslav Communism\n  | year = 1988\n  | location = Ithaca, New York\n  | publisher = Cornell University Press\n  | isbn = 978-0-8014-2186-0\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Barnett\n  | first = Neil\n  | title = Tito\n  | year = 2006\n  | publisher = Haus\n  | location = London, England\n  | isbn = 978-1-904950-31-8\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last=Belaj\n  | first=Marijana\n  | title=  'I'm not religious, but Tito is a God': Tito, Kumrovec, and the New Pilgrims \n  | pages=71\u201394\n  | work= Shrines and Pilgrimage in the Modern World: New Itineraries into the Sacred \n  | editor=  Peter Jan Margry\n  | year=2008\n  | publisher= Amsterdam University Press\n  | location= Amsterdam\n  | isbn= 978-90-485-0224-0\n}}\n* 