ting)</small>}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Stanoje Simi\u0107]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Borisav Risti\u0107]]|as=[[Ministry of Defense (Yugoslavia)#Ministers of the Army and Navy of the Kingdom of Yugoslavia in exile (1941)|Minister of the Army, Navy and Air Force]] of the [[Yugoslav government-in-exile]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Federal Secretary of People's Defense of Yugoslavia|Defence Minister of Yugoslavia]]|years=1945\u20131953}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ivan Go\u0161njak]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ivan Ribar]]|as=[[President of the Presidency of the People's Assembly]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[President of Yugoslavia]]|years=1953\u20131980\u00b2}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Lazar Koli\u0161evski]]|as=[[President of the Presidency of Yugoslavia]]}}\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Milan Gorki\u0107]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[President of the Presidency of the League of Communists of Yugoslavia]]|years=1937\u20131980<br><small>(acting before October 1940)</small>\n}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Branko Mikuli\u0107]]}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-new|title}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Marshal of Yugoslavia]]|years=1943\u20131980}}\n{{s-non|reason=Title Abolished}}\n{{s-dip}}\n{{s-new|office}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Non-Aligned Movement#Secretaries-General|Secretary-General of the Non-Aligned Movement]]|years=1961\u20131964}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Gamal Abdel Nasser]]}}\n{{s-ref|''i.e.'' [[Prime Minister of Yugoslavia]]|[[President for Life]] from 22 January 1974, died in office}}\n{{Federal Secretary of Foreign Affairs of SFRY}}\n{{Federal Secretary of People's Defense of SFRY}}\n{{Politburo of CK KPJ (1948-1952)}}\n{{Executive Committee of CK SKJ (1952-1958)}}\n{{Presidency of CK SKJ (1978-1982)}}\n{{Presidency of SFRY (1974-1979)}}\n{{Presidency of SFRY (1979-1984)}}\n{{SKJ Chairman}}\n{{Yugoslav Head of State}}\n{{Yugoslav Prime Minister}}\n{{NAMSecretary-General}}\n{{Resistance in Yugoslavia during Second World War}}\n{{People of the Yugoslav Front}}\n{{Leaders of the Ruling Parties of the Eastern Bloc}}\n{{President of the Federation of Veterans Associations