ling |editor1-first=Hans |editor2-last=Paabo |editor2-first=Katrin |date=1992 |title=Vem \u00e4r det: svensk biografisk handbok. 1993 |trans-title=Who is it: Swedish biographical handbook. 1993 |location=Stockholm |publisher=Norstedt |isbn=91-1-914072-X |language=Swedish |id={{LIBRIS|8261513}} |ref={{harvid|Uddling|Paabo|1992}}}}\n*{{cite encyclopedia |url=https://sok.riksarkivet.se/Sbl/Presentation.aspx?id=34857 |publisher=[[National Archives of Sweden]] |encyclopedia=[[Svenskt biografiskt lexikon]] |title=Nils Per Robert Swedlund |first=Kent |last=Zetterberg |year=2014 |volume=34 |page=542 |access-date=2017-12-15 |language=Swedish |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |date=1984 |title=Vem \u00e4r det: svensk biografisk handbok. 1985 |trans-title=Who is it: Swedish biographical handbook. 1985 |location=Stockholm |publisher=Norstedt |language=Swedish |isbn=91-1-843222-0 |id={{LIBRIS|3681527}} |ref={{harvid|Vem \u00e4r det|1984}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=https://www.un.org/en/peacekeeping/missions/untso/documents/untso_60_anniversary.pdf |publisher=[[United Nations]] |work=UNTSO News Magazine |title=UNITED NATIONS TRUCE SUPERVISION ORGANISATION 60th ANNIVERSARY |format=PDF |date=2008 |access-date=11 April 2017 |ref={{harvid|UNTSO News Magazine|2008}}}}\n*{{cite book |title=F\u00f6rsvarets traditioner i framtiden med \u00f6versiktlig historik fr\u00e5n 1500-talet |url=http://www.sfhm.se/contentassets/813daef056f04ee79a6cdca825daecdb/traditionsnamnden_forsvarets-traditioner-med-oversiktlig-historik-fran-1500-talet-reviderad-2016-05-24.pdf |year=2015 |publisher=Statens f\u00f6rsvarshistoriska museer TradN |language=Swedish |isbn=9789197859554 |id={{LIBRIS|17552963}} |access-date=11 April 2017 |ref={{harvid|F\u00f6rsvarets traditioner|2015}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412061852/http://www.sfhm.se/contentassets/813daef056f04ee79a6cdca825daecdb/traditionsnamnden_forsvarets-traditioner-med-oversiktlig-historik-fran-1500-talet-reviderad-2016-05-24.pdf |archive-date=12 April 2017 |url-status=dead }}\n\n*{{cite news |url=https://tidningar.kb.se/3678898/1970-01-10/edition/156590/part/1/page/5/?q=%22bo%20westin%22&from=1969-01-01&to=1971-12-31 |work=[[G\u00f6teborgs Handels- och Sj\u00f6fartstidning]] |title=Synnergren ny \u00d6B Lundvall marinchef |agency=TT |page=5 |date=10 January 1970 |accessdate=23 April 2020 |language=Swedish |ref={{harvid|GHT|1970}}}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{Staffs of the Swedish Armed Forces}}\n\n[[Category:Military appointments of Sweden]]\n[[Category:Chiefs of defence|Sweden]]\n[[Category:Chiefs of the Defence Staff (Sweden)| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox official post\n| post                     = Chief\n| body                     = the Defence Staff\n| native_name              = ''Chefen f\u00f6r f\u00f6rsvarsstaben''\n| insignia                 = \n| insigniasize             = \n| insigniacaption          = \n| flag                     = Naval Ensign of Sweden.svg\n| flagsize                 = \n| flagborder               = \n| flagcaption              = \n| image                    = \n| imagesize                = \n| alt                      = \n| incumbent                = \n| acting                   = \n| incumbentsince           = \n| department               = [[Ministry of Defence (Sweden)|Ministry of Defence]]\n| style                    = \n| type                     = Chief of the [[Defence Staff (Sweden)|Defence Staff]]\n| status                   = Abolished\n| abbreviation             = CFst\n| member_of                = \n| reports_to               = [[Supreme Commander of the Swedish Armed Forces]]\n| residence                = \n| seat                     = \u00d6stermalmsgatan 87, [[Stockholm]]\n| nominator                = \n| appointer                = \n| appointer_qualified      = \n| termlength               = [[At Her Majesty's pleasure]]\n| termlength_qualified     = \n| constituting_instrument  = \n| precursor                = [[General Staff (Sweden)#Chiefs of the General Staff|Chief of the General Staff]]\n| formation                = 1 July 1937\n| first                    = Major General [[Olof Th\u00f6rnell]]\n| last                     = Vice Admiral [[Peter Nordbeck (Swedish Navy officer)|Peter Nordbeck]]\n| abolished                = 1994\n| succession               = \n| unofficial_names         = ''F\u00f6rsvarsstabschef''\n| deputy                   = Vice Chief of the Defence Staff\n| salary                   = \n| website                  = \n}}\n\nThe '''Chief of the Defence Staff''' ({{lang-sv|Chefen f\u00f6r f\u00f6rsvarsstaben}}, CFst, or ''F\u00f6rsvarsstabschef'') was from 1937 to 1994 the second most senior member of the [[Swedish Armed Forces]] (after the [[Supreme Commander of the Swedish Armed Forces|Supreme Commander]]) and headed the [[Defence Staff (Sweden)|Defence Staff]]. The position was held by a senior member of one of the three main branches of the Swedish Armed Forces.\n\n==Chiefs of the Defence Staff==\n{{Officeholder table start\n| showorder                     = y\n| showimage                     = y\n| image_title                   = Portrait\n| officeholder_title            = Chief of the Defence Staff\n| showparty                     = n\n| showdefencebranch             = y\n| showtermlenght                = y\n| showref                       = y\n| showcabinet                   = y\n| cabinet_title                 = [[Prime Minister of Sweden|Prime Minister]]\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order                         = 1\n| image                         = O G Thornell.jpg\n| military_rank                 = Major general\n| officeholder                  = [[Olof Th\u00f6rnell]]\n| officeholder_sort             = Th\u00f6rnell, Olof\n| acting                        = \n| born_year                     = 1877\n| died_year                     = 1977\n| defence_branch                = <!--Army-->[[File:Arm\u00e9n vapen bra.svg|50px]]<br>[[Swedish Army|Army]]\n| term_start                    = 1 July 1937{{#tag:ref|On 1 July 1936, the then Inspector General of the Infantry, Major General Olof Th\u00f6rnell, was promoted to Lieutenant General and at the same time appointed Chief of the Defense Staff. Th\u00f6rnell now began the organization work. On 1 July 1937, the new staff gathered and the Chief of Defense Staff took command.<ref name=\"Furtenbach (1964), pp. 9, 11\">{{harvnb|Furtenbach|1964|pp=9, 11}}</ref>\n|group=note}}\n| term_end                      = December 1939{{#tag:ref|On 8 December 1939, Th\u00f6rnell was appointed [[Supreme Commander of the Swedish Armed Forces]]<ref name=\"\u00d6B i historien\">{{cite web |url=http://www.forsvarsmakten.se/sv/organisation/overbefalhavaren/overbefalhavaren-i-historien/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190504034305/http://www.forsvarsmakten.se/sv/organisation/overbefalhavaren/overbefalhavaren-i-historien/ |publisher=[[Swedish Armed Forces]] |title=\u00d6verbef\u00e4lhavare i historien |accessdate=2014-10-24 |archive-date=4 May 2019 |language=Swedish}}</ref> without at the same time appointing a new Chief of the Defence Staff.<ref>{{harvnb|Jarmar|2005|p=71}}</ref> After Th\u00f6rnell's appointment as Supreme Commander for the mobilized elements of the armed forces in December 1939, [[Axel Rappe (1884\u20131945)|Axel Rappe]] was appointed Deputy Chief of the Defence Staff. This meant that Rappe in reality served as Chief of the Defence Staff.<ref name=\"Cronenberg (1995-1997), p. 694\">{{harvnb|Cronenberg|1995\u20131997|p=694}}</ref>|group=note}}\n| timeinoffice                  = {{age in years|1937|1939}} years\n| ref                           = <ref name=\"Furtenbach (1964), pp. 9, 11\"/>\n| cabinet                       = [[Per Albin Hansson]]\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order                         = 2\n| image                         = Chief of the Defence Staff, Major General Axel Bredberg circa 1942.jpg\n| military_rank                 = Major general\n| officeholder                  = [[Axel Bredberg]] \n| offic